Events.RelatedDescription: Closed issue "Vue-router to fail gracefully when code-split deps fail to load" (#2067) at vuejs/vue-router
Events.RelatedBody:
### What problem does this feature solve?
When navigating to `https://vue-hn.now.sh/top` and if a specific code-split dependency fails to load, the url is changed to `https://vue-hn.now.sh`

steps to reproduce:
1. navigate to https://vue-hn.now.sh/top
2. developer tools > network tools > block url request 1.js
3. refresh https://vue-hn.now.sh/top
4. url is now https://vue-hn.now.sh


### What does the proposed API look like?
N/A
